{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/7422", "repo": "rails", "body": "@dhh I'll see what I can cook up when I get some time. I also pinged @radar for this thoughts.\n\nOff the top of my head, my thought is that it would be possible to use a concern to add groups of related routes against various things, but exclude some based on type.\n\n```ruby\nclass PurchasableConcern\n  RETURNABLES = Departments.map(&:name) - %w(pets electronics)\n\n  def self.call(mapper)\n    mapper.resources :purchases\n    mapper.resources :receipts\n    mapper.resources :returns if RETURNABLES.include?(mapper.current_scope[:controller])\n  end\nend\n```", "_id": {"$oid": "5237fbc3bd3543c15100b86e"}, "issue_id": 7422, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/7940218", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/7422#issuecomment-7940218", "updated_at": "2012-08-23T13:32:49Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ernie/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ernie/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ernie/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ernie/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/ernie", "login": "ernie", "gravatar_id": "2274a7476f6d2ac7aedcdec0651d0542", "html_url": "https://github.com/ernie", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ernie/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ernie/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ernie/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/2274a7476f6d2ac7aedcdec0651d0542?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F6a600c968f4e6a843dcaf600c1694e42.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ernie/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 14947, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ernie/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2012-08-22T16:30:49Z", "id": 7940218, "owner": "rails"}
